.TH SHUTDOWN 1m
.SH NAME
shutdown \- automatic shutdown procedure
.SH SYNOPSIS
shutdown
.SH DESCRIPTION
When shutting down one must:\ 
.in+5
a) make sure one is alone on the system. (Type "who")
.br
b) execute the "shutdown" command on the console
.br
c) wait for the # prompt to be printed
.br
d) type sync
.br
e) depress the halt key on the cpu
.SH "SEE ALSO"
apb(I)
